<use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tke1665702734474.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tke1665702734474.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tke1665702734474.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tke1665702734474\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      charset\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set default character set used by the Sybase open client.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"tke1665702734474__topic_d59288e1_d59289e1_d59290e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59291e1_d59292e1_d59293e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$SYB_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">charset</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">CharacterSetName</var> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tke1665702734474__section_qjz_zlw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d398018e72\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tke1665702734474__ul_p4z_1mw_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tke1665702734474__li_d26639e1_d26640e1_d26641e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59297e1_d59298e1_d59299e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">CharacterSetName</var>—name of a\n                  character set equivalent used by the Uniface application. This is the character\n                  set name and not the character set ID.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tke1665702734474__li_d26642e1_d26643e1_d26644e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59300e1_d59301e1_d59302e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>—disable character set\n                  conversion</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tke1665702734474__section_nrh_bmw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d398018e97\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59306e1_d59307e1_d59308e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">charset</span> option when you\n            need to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"tke1665702734474__ul_yyv_cmw_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tke1665702734474__li_d26645e1_d26646e1_d26647e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59309e1_d59310e1_d59311e1\">Convert the client default character set in\n                  Sybase to a set which is equivalent to that used by Uniface.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tke1665702734474__li_d26648e1_d26649e1_d26650e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59312e1_d59313e1_d59314e1\">Use Unicode characters in the SQL Workbench,\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript statement, or error messages. In this case,\n                  specify <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">unicode</span> connector option and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">charset\n                     ut8</span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tke1665702734474__section_z5z_dmw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d398018e133\">Character Set Conversion</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59318e1_d59319e1_d59320e1\">Uniface and the Sybase Open Client Library\n            (Client-Library) may use different character sets. When this happens, the connector must\n            convert the client default character set in Sybase to a set which is equivalent to that\n            used by Uniface.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59321e1_d59322e1_d59323e1\">If you do not use this connector option, Uniface\n            assumes that the Uniface character set matches the Sybase character set, or that the\n            conversion is performed by Sybase.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59324e1_d59325e1_d59326e1\">You can check whether character set conversion is\n            performed with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">select @@char_convert</code> query. This query can be\n            issued from within the Uniface SQL Workbench, or by the Sybase ISQL tool. If the query\n            returns 0, no conversion is performed. If it returns 1, conversion is performed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59327e1_d59328e1_d59329e1\">You can check the client’s default character set with\n            the <code class=\"ph codeph\">select @@client_csname</code> query. Possible return values depend on your\n            installed character set. For example, ISO_1 and CP850.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59330e1_d59331e1_d59332e1\">You can check the server’s default character set with\n            the <code class=\"ph codeph\">sp_helpsort</code> stored procedure.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tke1665702734474__section_ndg_gmw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d398018e164\">Disable Character Set Conversion</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tke1665702734474__p_d59336e1_d59337e1_d59338e1\">When the Sybase Client and Sybase SQL Server are\n            configured for different character sets, Sybase SQL Server performs automatic character\n            set conversion. In some situations, this conversion is not recommended. Therefore,\n            character set conversion can be disabled with the following SYB connector option:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tke1665702734474__pre_pcr_hmw_jcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">USYS$SYB_PARAMS charset off</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tke1665702734474__section_xnz_hmw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d398018e177\">Example: Enabling Unicode Support</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"tke1665702734474__pre_lzj_kmw_jcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">usys$syb_params charset utf8, unicode, smp, keyword</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlc1665702735327.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>unicode</a><p>Enable or disable Unicode support in the SYB connector.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "charset Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 charset Set default character set used by the Sybase open client. USYS$SYB_PARAMS = charset CharacterSetName | off Arguments CharacterSetName —name of a character set equivalent used by the Uniface application. This is the character set name and not the character set ID. off —disable character set conversion Description Use the charset option when you need to: Convert the client default character set in Sybase to a set which is equivalent to that used by Uniface. Use Unicode characters in the SQL Workbench, sql ProcScript statement, or error messages. In this case, specify unicode connector option and charset ut8 . Character Set Conversion Uniface and the Sybase Open Client Library (Client-Library) may use different character sets. When this happens, the connector must convert the client default character set in Sybase to a set which is equivalent to that used by Uniface. If you do not use this connector option, Uniface assumes that the Uniface character set matches the Sybase character set, or that the conversion is performed by Sybase. You can check whether character set conversion is performed with the select @@char_convert query. This query can be issued from within the Uniface SQL Workbench, or by the Sybase ISQL tool. If the query returns 0, no conversion is performed. If it returns 1, conversion is performed. You can check the client’s default character set with the select @@client_csname query. Possible return values depend on your installed character set. For example, ISO_1 and CP850. You can check the server’s default character set with the sp_helpsort stored procedure. Disable Character Set Conversion When the Sybase Client and Sybase SQL Server are configured for different character sets, Sybase SQL Server performs automatic character set conversion. In some situations, this conversion is not recommended. Therefore, character set conversion can be disabled with the following SYB connector option: USYS$SYB_PARAMS charset off Copy Example: Enabling Unicode Support usys$syb_params charset utf8, unicode, smp, keyword Copy Related Links unicode Enable or disable Unicode support in the SYB connector. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}